      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 2) SAR REASONING (why features affect CYP2D6 inhibition)\nCYP2D6 inhibitors commonly present:\n- A **strongly basic, accessible cationic center** (often **tertiary amine**) that can engage **Asp301** (key acidic residue in CYP2D6 binding site).\n- One or more **hydrophobic/aromatic rings** positioned to occupy lipophilic pockets.",
      "tool_name": null,
