      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "This molecule:\n- Will be predominantly **zwitterionic** at pH 7.4 (\u2013NH3\u207a and \u2013COO\u207b). The **positive charge exists**, but it is **attenuated/\u201cinternally paired\u201d** by the nearby carboxylate, reducing the \u201cfree\u201d cationic character and often **reducing CYP2D6 affinity** versus a lipophilic tertiary amine.\n- Has **one aromatic system (indole)**, but overall polarity is high due to the amino acid functionality, which tends to **lower membrane partitioning and CYP binding**.\n- The **basic center is primary** and adjacent to a carbonyl/carboxylate system; many potent CYP2D6 inhibitors are more **hydrophobic** and have **bulkier tertiary amines**.",
      "tool_name": null,
