      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 3) MECHANISTIC BASIS (interaction with CYP2D6)\n- **Potential binding mode:** the **protonated amine** could, in principle, ion-pair with **Asp301**, while the **indole** sits in a hydrophobic region.\n- **Limiting factors mechanistically:**\n  - The **carboxylate** can create unfavorable electrostatics/desolvation penalties in the largely hydrophobic active site and can reduce effective binding of the cation to Asp301.\n  - The molecule is relatively **small and polar**, which often correlates with **weaker reversible inhibition** of CYP2D6 compared with classic basic, lipophilic inhibitors.",
